full_content.content: Common reasons your Whirlpool cooktop is not working
The most common reasons your Whirlpool cooktop is not working are a defective electronic control board, broken igniter or a faulty infinite switch.
We can help! Our service technicians have repaired over
Whirlpool cooktops. We can fix yours no matter where you bought it.
Most common repairs needed to fix a Whirlpool cooktop

When the cooktop is not working, a defective electronic control board could be failing to send current to surface elements. Electrical relays close contacts to send current to a burner when you set a burner to heat. When the internal logic or internal circuits in the electronic control board fail, current won’t flow to the burners. When your cooktop has power but none of the elements work, have a Sears Home Services Technician check the electronic control board and replace it if it’s defective.

A broken igniter prevent burners from lighting on the cooktop. Some cooktops use an ignition system that reignites burners when the control doesn’t detect a flame on a burner in use. When a cooktop uses electronics to sense a burner flame, a broken igniter can short out electronics or damage other components in the burner ignition system so the cooktop won’t work. Have a Sears Home Services Appliance Repair Technician examine and repair your cooktop when it isn’t working.
Why won't my cooktop burners ignite?

When the cooktop is not working, you may find that the problem is caused by a faulty infinite switch. The infinite switch has electrical contacts that turn a surface element on and off and controls the heat level of the element. When internal switch contacts short out, the electrical circuit breaker will trip and prevent the cooktop from getting power. When you’re unable to reset the circuit breaker because it trips again as soon as try to reset it, you can suspect that faulty infinite switch may be preventing the cooktop from working. Have a Sears Home Services Technician examine and repair your cooktop.

full_content.content: Reset the house circuit breaker for the cooktop. This may restore electrical power so the cooktop begins working again.
If you have a gas cooktop, check the electrical outlet using this process:
Plug a nightlight or small appliance into the electrical outlet to check for power.
If the electrical outlet is dead, have an electrician fix the issue.
If the outlet has power, you’ll likely need to have a service technician repair the cooktop failure.
For a gas cooktop that has electrical power but burners won’t light, check the gas supply cut-off valve to make sure that it’s fully open.
Check the gas supply for other gas appliances in your home. If your entire home is without a gas supply, contact your gas supplier to fix that problem.
When your gas cooktop has power but the burners won’t spark to ignite when you turn on a burner, you may need to replace the spark igniter.

The spark module receives a signal from the burner switches and sends voltage to the igniter electrodes to make them spark to ignite the surface burner. If the spark module isn't sending voltage to the burners, replace the spark module.
Follow the steps in this illustrated repair guide to replace the spark module in a gas cooktop:
How to Replace the Spark Module in a Gas Cooktop
If these tips don’t help you find and fix the cause of your cooktop failure, schedule
service and we’ll send a technician to your home to resolve the issue.
What to expect when you experience a Whirlpool cooktop not working issue
How is the not working problem fixed?

Correcting most not working problems usually involves replacing the electronic control board, igniter or infinite switch. However, there are many potential causes, so a thorough diagnosis is key to fixing the problem. An accurate diagnosis is essential to understanding how much the repair will be.
Sears Home Services recommendations for a cooktop that is not working

When the cooktop is not working it can be for many reasons. To avoid replacing unneeded parts we recommend having a Sears Home Services professional perform diagnostic tests to identify the root cause of the problem. Our technicians are experienced at diagnosing all types of cooktop failures.
What to look out for with a cooktop not working diagnosis

Diagnosing modern appliances without proper knowledge and training can be difficult. Without using proper diagnostic techniques, fixing your cooktop problem will only be achieved through changing parts on a hunch. Appliances, especially in the last 10 years, have become extremely advanced, and many models have electronic parts that are difficult to test. DIY repairs on the latest appliance models are becoming increasingly difficult.

full_content.content: Why isn’t my Whirlpool cooktop working?
A faulty circuit breaker, malfunctioning burner switch, or damaged burner element can cause the cooktop to stop working. Inspect these parts for issues.
Could a tripped circuit breaker prevent my Whirlpool cooktop from working?
Yes, a tripped circuit breaker can disrupt power to the cooktop. Resetting the breaker should restore power to the unit.
How can I fix a Whirlpool cooktop that isn’t turning on?
Check the power supply, burner switches, and control board for any malfunctions. Replacing faulty parts should restore functionality.
What should I do if my Whirlpool cooktop still isn’t working after checking the power supply?
If the cooktop isn’t working after verifying the power, the issue may lie with the control board or wiring, requiring a technician’s inspection.

A drop-in range is a type of kitchen stove that is designed to be fitted into a pre-existing space in kitchen cabinetry, mounted on a platform, flanked by cabinetry, and often featuring a custom panel at the bottom.
What is a Dual Fuel Range?
A dual fuel range combines the precision of an electric oven with the responsiveness of a gas cooktop, offering the best of both worlds for cooking enthusiasts.
